Center: Centre for Photonuclear Experiments Data, Moscow State University, Russia
ref: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.14, Issue.2, p.456 (1976)
title: Photoproton cross section and angular distributions for 12C in the giant dipole resonance region.

x4freetext: Photoproton cross section and  angular  distributions
for 12C in the giant dipole resonance region.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.14, Issue.2, p.456 (1976)

x4freetext: Bremsstrahlung  beam  was  hardened  by a
19.5 cm graphite cylinder, located directly in front
of the antiscattering collimator.
Ground state transition assumed.
Uncooled  Si(Li) solid state detectors with an
active area of 200 mm**2 and thickness of 3 mm.
As target material 6 cm x 10 cm polystyrene foil with
a thickness of 3.33 mg/cm**2 was used.

reacs.QuantHlp: Differential c/s with respect to angle

x4freetext: The absolute   differential  cross  sections  of  the
12C(g,p)11B reaction,  taken at the seven angles, as
a function  of  lab  energy  were  derived  from the
protoproton spectra measured with the target  at  80
deg with the respect to the forward photon beam.
